Title: Human-Operated Ransomware Impact via PsExec and PsShutdown

Description: >
  Detects a correlated sequence of PsExec service creation followed by PsShutdown
  service creation within a short timeframe, commonly observed during the impact
  phase of human-operated ransomware attacks.

references:
  - https://www.mandiant.com/resources/blog/ransomware-attack-lifecycle
  - https://www.crowdstrike.com/blog/big-game-hunting-with-ryuk-ransomware/
  - https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1489/
logsource:
  product: windows

detection:
  psexec_service:
    EventID: 7045
    ServiceName|contains: 'PSEXESVC'

  psshutdown_service:
    EventID: 7045
    ServiceName: PsShutdownSvc

  condition: psexec_service followed_by psshutdown_service within 5m

falsepositives:
  - Approved IT maintenance using Sysinternals
level: high

tags:
  - attack.impact
  - attack.t1489
  - attack.t1569.002
  - attack.t1021
